<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧱 M000 Week 4 — English Worksheet (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> House Walls (No Roof) · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 38 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set of steps. Before you imagine the agent doing it, write what you think will happen.</p>
<pre><code>repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What does the agent build? Write one sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    move up by 1
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Is this a wall lying flat on the ground, or standing up tall? How tall is it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>repeat 3 times:
    repeat 8 times:
        place block down
        move up by 1
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The agent runs the inside loop, then the outside loop. What shape does it finish with? About how many blocks did it place?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each block below is meant to do something, but it is broken. The goal is written first. Read the goal, then find the bug, fix the code, and explain in one short sentence why your fix works.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — Goal: a single wall that is <strong>8 blocks long</strong> on the ground. <em>Hint: count how many times the loop runs.</em></p>
<pre><code>repeat 7 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does your fix work? One sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — Goal: build <strong>two walls</strong> — a wall 8 blocks long, then turn right once, then another wall 8 blocks long. <em>Hint: the turn should happen only one time, not on every loop.</em></p>
<pre><code>repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    move forward
    turn right
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does your fix work? One sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Goal: a wall that is <strong>8 blocks long AND 8 blocks tall</strong> — a square of blocks. <em>Hint: you need one loop inside another loop.</em></p>
<pre><code>repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    move up by 1
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does your fix work? One sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The agent should build one wall, turn right, then build a second wall. Two lines are missing. Fill them in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code>repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    move forward
____________
repeat 8 times:
    place block down
    ____________
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>turn right</code> · <code>move up by 1</code> · <code>move forward</code> · <code>place block down</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the two missing lines and say why you chose each one.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your homework world. Build your house walls with <strong>no roof yet</strong> — about 8 blocks long and 8 blocks tall, using two loops. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your house, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 3 or 4 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>First, I …</p>
<p>My first loop did …</p>
<p>My second loop did …</p>
<p>The hardest part was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you walk around your house. Talk through it like you are teaching a friend who has never seen it. Try to use these words: <strong>loop</strong>, <strong>repeat</strong>, <strong>block</strong>, <strong>wall</strong>, <strong>bug</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show the outside and say how long and how tall it is.</li>
<li>Read your two loops out loud and say what each one does.</li>
<li>Show one bug you hit and how you fixed it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Plan it here first — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
